column5: Hi all,Well as usual I was working the morning of walleye opener, but luckily I live on a great walleye lake so I snuck down the front lawn at daybreak and cast for a couple hors before work.When I got back from work I did the same thing for a couple of hours and was again rewarded with some solid fishing.All the fish were spawned out. Kept 4 for some food and released a bunch.Fish were as deep as 9 feet and as shallow as 1 foot.Slip bobber the most effective method by far, bait medium minnows.Click the link below for the Youtube video.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tg3PHDXVlrw
Thanks for sharing, looks like a great start for the season
Awesome shots in the early morning sunrise. Thanks for sharing!
Thanks for sharing the video. You are a lucky guy to be able to walk out the front door and do that.
Limeyanger- sent you a pm too.Great video, by the way! Looks like the dog had fun too!
Looks like a rough place to live!
Yeah, but i'll take one for the team eh.
